com.jgaap.generics
Class Language

java.lang.Object
  com.jgaap.generics.Language
All Implemented Interfaces:
Displayable, java.lang.Comparable<Language>
Direct Known Subclasses:
Arabic, Chinese, ChineseBMM, ChineseFMM, ChineseJointMM, ComputerLanguage, English, Generic
public abstract class Language
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Language>, Displayable

This class was designed to make the implementation of languages in jgaap as simple as possible. All that is needed to make a new language is to make a new class in the com.jgaap.languages package that extends com.jgaap.generics.Language all that you need is to send the constructor to the super class specifying the name - how users will see the language displayed, language - the way the internal system and other classes will view the language (all lowercase), and the charset- the character set you will read in when working with this language. If the language you are working with requires pre-processing before it is handed off to jgaap that can be defined in the parse method you can choose to override. If you are doing parsing you MUST add super.setParseable(true) to your constructor.

Since:
4.x
Author:
Michael Ryan

Define the language to read documents in and which methods of jgaap's can be used on them.

Parameters:
name - - display name of language (user visable)
